#: ../../manual/lighting/lamps/area.rst:87
msgid ""
"Choosing the appropriate shape for your :guilabel:`Area` light will enhance "
"the believability of your scene. For example, you may have an indoor scene "
"and would like to simulate light entering through a window. You could place "
"a :guilabel:`Rectangular` area lamp in a window (vertical) or from neons "
"(horizontal) with proper ratios for :guilabel:`Size X` and :guilabel:`Size "
"Y`. For the simulation of the light emitted by a TV screen a vertical "
":guilabel:`Square` area lamp would be better in most cases."
msgstr ""
